description:
RadioEquipmentClock: Table storing radio equipment clock synchronization parameters and configuration for each cell, including timestamps, cell identifiers, and various alarm and quality settings.
dateTime: Timestamp of the recorded data.
Area_Name: Geographic area of the cell site.
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (appears identical to CellId).
Id3:  Redundant identifier (appears constant).
Id4: Redundant identifier (appears constant).
vsDataType: Data type identifier.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
RadioEquipmentClock.selectionProcessMode: Mode for clock selection process.
RadioEquipmentClock.syncInconsistentConfigAlarmEnabled: Flag indicating if the synchronization inconsistency alarm is enabled.
RadioEquipmentClock.minQualityLevel: Minimum acceptable quality level for the clock.
RadioEquipmentClock.timeHoldoverAlarmConfig: Configuration for time holdover alarms.
RadioEquipmentClock.freqDeviationThreshold: Threshold for frequency deviation alarms.
RadioEquipmentClock.bfnOffset:  Offset for the base frequency number.
RadioEquipmentClock.radioEquipmentClockId: Identifier for the specific radio equipment clock.
